problem link : https://leetcode.com/problems/longest-palindrome/description/

Intuition
A palindrome has the property that every character appears an even number of times , except for one character taht appears an odd number of times that occupy centre of palindrome.

i first count the freq of every character using a hash map .

then i iterate through the freq map :

if a character has an even frequency , i add all of its occurences to the answer since they can be placed symmetrically in the palindrome.
if a character has an odd freq i add it's largest even contribution (freq -1) to the answer and mark that an odd freq exists.

after processing all characters if at least one odd freq was found , i add 1 to the result to place one of the remaining odd characters at the centre of palindrome.

Complexity
Time complexity:
O(n)
Building the frequency map takes O(n).
Traversing the frequency map takes O(k), where k is the number of distinct characters.
Overall complexity is O(n)

Space complexity:
O(k)
Where k is the number of distinct characters stored in the hash map.

Code
class Solution:
    def longestPalindrome(self, s: str) -> int:
        freq = {}
        for ch in s:
            freq[ch] = freq.get(ch,0) + 1
        odd = False
        result = 0
        for ch in freq:
            if freq[ch] % 2 == 0:
                result += freq[ch]
            else:
                odd = True
                result += freq[ch] - 1
        return result + 1 if odd else result
